ie\n| {{Nom}}\n|-\t\n|rowspan=\"13\"| 2011\n|rowspan=\"5\"| [[37th People's Choice Awards|People's Choice Awards]]\n| Favorite Action Movie\n|rowspan=\"2\"| ''Iron Man 2''\n| {{Won}}\n|rowspan=\"5\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref name=\"PCAnoms\" />\n|-\n|Favorite Movie\n|{{Nom}}\n|-\n|Favorite Movie Actor\n|Robert Downey Jr.\n|{{Nom}}\n|-\n|Favorite Action Star\n|Robert Downey Jr.\n|{{Nom}}\n|-\n|Favorite On-Screen Team\n|Robert Downey Jr. and Don Cheadle\n|{{Nom}}\n|-\n|[[83rd Academy Awards|Academy Awards]]\n| [[Academy Award for Best Visual Effects|Best Visual Effects]]\n| ''Iron Man 2''\n|{{Nom}}\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref name=\"Oscarnom\" />\n|-\n|rowspan=\"4\"| [[37th Saturn Awards|Saturn Awards]]\n| [[Saturn Award for Best Science Fiction Film|Best Science Fiction Film]]\n| ''Iron Man 2''\n|{{Nom}}\n|rowspan=\"4\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref name=\"Saturnnoms\" />\n|-\n| [[Saturn Award for Best Actor|Best Actor]]\n|Robert Downey Jr.\n|{{Nom}}\n|-\n| [[Saturn Award for Best Supporting Actress|Best Supporting Actress]]\n|Scarlett Johansson\n|{{Nom}}\n|-\n| [[Saturn Award for Best Special Effects|Best Special Effects]]\n| ''Iron Man 2''\n|{{Nom}}\n|-\n|rowspan=\"3\"|[[9th Visual Effects Society Awards|Visual Effects Society Awards]]\n|Outstanding Visual Effects in a Visual Effects-Driven Feature Motion Picture\n|[[Ben Snow]], [[Ged Wright]], [[Janek Sirrs]], Susan Pickett\n|{{nom}}\n|rowspan=\"3\"|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.visualeffectssociety.com/ayear/9th-annual-ves-awards|title=9th Annual VES Awards|work=visual effects society|accessdate=December 22, 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n|Outstanding Models in a Feature Motion Picture\n|Bruce Holcomb, Ron Woodall, John Goodson, John Walker for \"Hammer Military Drones\"\n|{{nom}}\n|-\n|Outstanding Created Environment in a Feature Motion Picture\n|Giles Hancock, Richard Bluff, Todd Vaziri, Aaron McBride for the \"Stark Expo\"\n|{{nom}}\n|}\n\n==Sequel==\n{{main|Iron Man 3}}\n{{further|List of Marvel Cinematic Universe films}}\nAfter the release of ''Iron Man 2'', [[Walt Disney Studios (division)|Walt Disney Studios]] agreed to pay Paramount at least $115 million for the worldwide distribution rights to ''Iron Man 3'' and ''The Avengers''.<ref name=\"DisneyIM3\" /> Disney, Marvel and Paramount announced a May 3, 2013 release date for ''Iron Man 3''.<ref name=\"IM3ReleaseDate\" /> Shane Black directed ''Iron Man 3'',<ref name=\"ShaneBlackIM3\" /> from a screenplay by [[Drew Pearce]].<ref name=\"DrewPearceIM3\" /> Downey, Paltrow, Cheadle, and Favreau reprised their roles, while [[Ben Kingsley]]<ref name=\"KingsleyIM3\" /> played [[Trevor Slattery]],<ref name=\"MandarinIM3\" /> [[Guy Pearce]] played [[Aldrich Killian]],<ref name=\"GuyPearceIM3\" /> and [[Rebecca Hall]]<ref name=\"HallIM3\" /> played [[Maya Hansen]].<ref name=\"HansenIM3\" />\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of films featuring powered exoskeletons]]\n\n==Notes==\n{{Reflist|group=N}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|refs=\n<ref name=\"EWHoward\">{{Cite news |url=https://ew.com/article/2008/11/04/iron-man-2-why-terrence-howard-was-recast/ |title='Iron Man 2': How Terrence Howard Lost His Metal |last=Sperling |first=Nicole |work=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|date=November 4, 2008 |accessdate=November 1, 2008 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150221142150/https://ew.com/article/2008/11/04/iron-man-2-why-terrence-howard-was-recast/ |archivedate=February 21, 2015 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"THRReview\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/review/iron-man-2-film-review-29527 |title=Iron Man 2 \u2013 Film Review |last=Honeycutt |first=Kirk |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]| date=April 27, 2010 |accessdate=April 27, 2010 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101124091051/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/review/iron-man-2-film-review-29527|archivedate=November 24, 2010|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=commentary>''Iron Man 2'' DVD commentary with [[Jon Favreau]]</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"IMDBSoundtracks\">{{cite web| url=https://www.imdb.com/title/tt1228705/soundtrack |title=Iron Man 2 (2010) \u2013 Soundtracks |website=[[IMDb]] |accessdate=November 29, 2011}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"ViralMarketingApplication\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.starkindustriesnow.com/ |title=Stark Industries |publisher=starkindustriesnow.com |accessdate=March 11, 2010 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100701202658/http://www.starkindustriesnow.com/ |archivedate=July 1, 2010}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"novel\">{{Cite book |last=Irvine |first=Alex |title=''Iron Man 2'' |publisher=[[Del Rey Books|Del Rey]] |year=2010 |ISBN=978-0-446-56458-8 |url-access=registration |url=https://archive.org/details/ironman200irvi }}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Highest2010Grosses\">{{Cite web| url=https://boxofficemojo.com/yearly/chart/?yr=2010&p=.htm |title=2010 DOMESTIC GROSSES |work=[[Box Office Mojo]] |publisher=Amazon.com |accessdate=November 29, 2012}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"International2010Grosses\">{{Cite web| url=https://boxofficemojo.com/yearly/chart/?view2=worldwide&yr=2010&p=.htm |title=2010 WORLDWIDE GROSSES |work=[[Box Office Mojo]] |publisher=Amazon.com |accessdate=November 29, 2012}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Eric Vespe\">{{Cite news|first=Eric |last=Vespe |date=February 9, 2007 |title=Quint visits the IRON MAN production offices! Art! Favreau speaks about sequels (?!?), casting and more!!! |work=[[Ain't It Cool News]] |url=https://www.aintitcool.com/node/31525 |accessdate=March 30, 2009 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6A5kiyLe4?url=http://www.aintitcool.com/node/31525 |archivedate=August 21, 2012 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"FavreauStarWars\">{{Cite news|first=Rob |last=Worley |authorlink=Rob Worley |date=September 8, 2007 |title=Iron Man: Favreau on films, fans, and Fin Fang Foom |work=Mania |url=http://www.mania.com/iron-man-favreau-film-fans-fin-fang-foom_article_90337.html |accessdate=March 30, 2009 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6AADgB79W?url=http